  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      20 subjects presenting with horizontal mandibular ridge width less than 5 mm were selected
      and randomly divided two groups (10 in each group). the first group received interpositional
      block grafts (harvested from the chin and ramus) covered with Platelet-rich fibrin membrane.
      the second group received onlay block grafts (harvested from the chin and ramus) and covered
      with Platelet-rich fibrin membrane. the grafts are left for 4 months. the alveolar ridge
      width dimensions is then measured using radiographic analysis using cone-beam computed
      tomography scans
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
